<article id="post-1828" class="post-1828 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized">
	<div class="blog-item-wrap">
				<a href="http://portcolbornelibrary.org/?p=1828" title="New Adult Programs" >
			 				</a>
		<div class="post-inner-content">
			<header class="entry-header page-header">

				<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://portcolbornelibrary.org/?p=1828" rel="bookmark">New Adult Programs</a></h1>

								<div class="entry-meta">
					<span class="posted-on"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> <a href="http://portcolbornelibrary.org/?p=1828" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2016-04-21T14:06:36+00:00">April 21, 2016</time></a></span><span class="byline"> <i class="fa fa-user"></i> <span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://portcolbornelibrary.org/?author=1">admin</a></span></span>
				
				</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
							</header><!-- .entry-header -->

						<div class="entry-content">

					<h3>“MAESTRA”— A Documentary Film Presented by the Canadian-Cuban Friendship Association of Niagara</h3>
<p><strong>Tuesday, May 17, 2016, 6:30 &#8211; 7:30 p.m.</strong></p>
<p>In Cuba, 1961, 250,000 volunteers taught 700,000 people to read and write in one year. 100,000 of the teachers were under 18 years old. Over half were women. MAESTRA explores this story through the personal testimonies of the young women who went out to teach literacy in rural communities across the island—and found themselves deeply transformed in the process.</p>
<p>FREE. Space is limited. Reserve your seat. Tickets available at the library.</p>
<hr />
<h3></h3>
<h3>“The Stand at Fort Erie Against the Fenians”— 150th Anniversary of the Fenian Raids</h3>
<p><strong>Tuesday, May 24, 2016, 6:00 &#8211; 7:00 p.m. </strong></p>
<p>With local author June Chipp. Sign up for this informative presentation on the Fenian invasion and the fight that took place in the village of Fort Erie on June 2, 1866. June’s book, <em><strong>Duty and Honour: the Stand Against the Fenians in Fort Erie</strong></em>, tells this compelling story and contains information about the fight that was previously unknown.</p>
<p>FREE. Space is limited. Pre-register. Tickets at the Library.</p>
<hr />
<h3>“The 32 Second Entrepreneur”— Small Business Success</h3>
<p><strong>Tuesday, May 31, 6:00 &#8211; 7:30 p.m. </strong></p>
<p>With local author Dan Barrett. Join business consultant Dan Barrett as he gives practical and concise advice for opening and operating a successful business.</p>
<p>FREE. Space is limited. Pre-register. Tickets at the Library.</p>
<hr />
<h3>Estate Planning Series— “Understanding Probate”</h3>
<p><strong>Thursday, June 2, 2016, 6:00 &#8211; 7:30 p.m. </strong></p>
<p>With local author Larry Fisher. Sign up soon for the latest session in Larry’s informative series on estate planning. This session focuses on probate.</p>
<p>FREE. Space is limited. Pre-register. Tickets at the Library.</p>
<hr />
<h3>Plein Air Painting for Adults—Outdoor Art Classes with Instructor Mary Unrau</h3>
<p><strong>Watercolours: Mondays, 2:00 &#8211; 4:00 p.m., starting May 16, 2016 </strong></p>
<p><strong>Acrylics: Tuesdays, 2:00 &#8211; 4:00 p.m., starting May 17, 2016 </strong></p>
<p>Cost is $10.00 per person. Pay as you go, or pre-pay in advance. Participants are to bring their own materials.</p>
<p>Contact Mary for more information and guidance on what supplies you need at 905-894- 8199 or maryunrau@live.com</p>

				<p><a class="btn btn-default read-more" href="http://portcolbornelibrary.org/?p=1828" title="New Adult Programs">Read More</a></p>

							</div><!-- .entry-content -->
					</div>
	</div>
</article><!-- #post-## -->

			
				
